    "LSTM (Hochreiter and Schmidhuber 1997) incorporates a memory cell, which enables the network to learn when to forget, ignore, or store information in the memory cell.",
    "The forget gate (f t) allows the memory cell to reset the cell state, the input gate (i t) is responsible for how much of the input node's (ct) value should be added to the cell state (c t).",
    "The output gate (o t) determines how to update the values of the hidden units.",
    "This mechanism helps mitigate the vanishing and exploding gradient problems in RNNs.",
    "The functions of LSTM are computed as follows"
  ],
